    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-06-25T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-06-25T18:00:00-05:00" n="139"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d139">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.AA/6–2548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Acting United States Representative at the United Nations</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Jessup</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-06-25T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 25, 1948—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>432. <gloss target="#t_reurtel1">Reurtel</gloss> 815 June 24 you are authorized
                    support Ceylon application for membership <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>.
                    Dept preparing statement re Ceylon application which you may make on appropriate
                        occasion.<note n="1" xml:id="d139fn1">In a meeting on August 18 the Security
                        Council considered the report of its Committee on the Admission of New
                        Members, concerning the application of Ceylon; and the first statement was
                        made by the U.S. Representative at the United Nations, Ambassador Warren R.
                        Austin. The Security Council failed to take favorable action in recommending
                        Ceylon for membership, since a negative vote was cast by a permanent member.
                        For the proceedings of the meeting on this matter, see United Nations, <hi
                            rend="italic">Official Records of the Security Council, Third Year, No.
                            105</hi>, pp. 3 ff. For the brief special report submitted by the
                        Security Council to the General Assembly on the subject, see United Nations
                        document A/618, August 23, 1948.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshal</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
